622 U2770
This course provides an overview to analytical techniques in handling spatial data, especially patterns analysis for vector-base data type. It will cover theories and applications of these analytical techniques, including basic statistical techniques for describing, modeling, and analyzing spatial patterns. The objective is to learn and employ a diverse and powerful set of techniques for gaining more insight into geographical processes and patterns.
