B00 U0120
This course aims to equip students with knowledge and techniques they need to write an academic research paper, primarily through an introduction to features of academic English and to the framework of each part of the paper. They will also learn how to give an effective presentation of their research.
Week	Topic
Week 1	Course Introduction
Week 2	[Unit 1] An approach to academic writing
Week 3	[Unit 2] Writing general to specific texts
Week 4	[Unit 3] SPSE
Week 5	Writing Introductions
Week 6	Writing Literature Reviews I
Week 7	Writing Literature Reviews II
Week 8	Peer Review and Discussion
Week 9	Writing Summaries and Paraphrases
Week 10	[Unit 7] Writing Methods
Week 11	[Unit 4] Data commentary
Week 12	[Unit 7] Results
Week 13	[Unit 8] Discussions
Week 14	Writing Conclusions
Week 15	How to present your work
Week 16	Writing Abstracts
Week 17	Overall Review and Individual Consultation
Week 17	Poster Presentations
