B21 M0380
Developmental Biology is a convenional and facinating field of biology. It involves in the studies of embryonic and postembryonic development. sexual maturation, reproduction and aging. The revolution of technologies in molecular and celluar biology as well as microscopy has greatly accelerate the research in the field. Thus, the students in this course will be asked to read , dissect and present the most recent published papers in the field.
