B21 U1700
The role of RNA in regulating gene expression has become a topic of intense interest. This course will focus on RNA research explore and discuss the methods whereby RNA can regulate gene expression with examples in various model systems, including yeast, Drosophila, mammals, and viral infection. The course will also highlight the application of this knowledge in therapeutics and research at the final section.
</>
