<c>
B44 U1600
This course is to introduce the fundamentals and methodology on research of molecular evolution. We will introduce the evolutionary changes and patterns of sequences, methods for phylogenetic analyses, and inferring sites under positive selection. Topics on recent advances of molecular evolution studies will be offered at the end, on phylogenomics, horizontal gene transfer, and genome evolution. Students are highly recommended to take evolution, genetics or equivalent subjects before taking this course. Laboratory practices will offered for students to be familiar with data retrieving and analyses. Homework assignments will be distributed weekly, which require substantial extra work time.
</>
<c>
B44 U1680
主要依上年B441620潮間帶生態學為藍本，以英文授課型式介紹潮間帶生態學，並在課程中以堂課在和平島海濱公園岩岸之生物及調察方法。學生學習方法包括聽課，小組討論及撰寫報告。
This course will be based on the last year’s Intertidal Ecology (B441620), being conducted in English to teach the basic intertidal ecology and use this system as examples to introduce the basic concepts in population and community ecology, common research methods, statistical techniques and writing skills in ecological studies. This course has 3 lessons based in Wa-Zhi-Wei and He-Ping-Dao to observe intertidal organisms and introduce the basic field techiniques in intertidal ecological studies.
Contents:
1.	General introduction to ecological patterns and processes
2.	Tides
3.	Waves
4.	Rocky shores
5.	Field observation at He Ping Dao
6.	Group discussion on data
7.	Sandy shores
8.	Field observation at Wa Zhi Wei
9.	Group discussion on data
10.	Mangroves
11.	Field observation at Wa Zhi Wei
12.	Group discussion on data
13.	Factors affecting vertical and horizontal distribution of intertidal organisms
14.	Predator and prey relationships on coastal ecology
15.	Skills in writing and reading marine biology paper 1
16.	Skills in writing and reading marine biology paper 2
17.	Discussion 1
18.	Discussion 2
19.	Student presentation
</>
