B46 M1370
以Annual Review of Biochemistry每年所登刊的知名生化學家自傳為本，搜尋有關資料，包括研究論文，介紹他們成長過程中學術發展的時空背景。並詳述他們的學術生涯和人文素養。最後，由至今所累積的生化原理和觀念，評論他們的成就於生化學界的貢獻。以及他們的奮鬥對後輩研究人員的啟發。
</>
<c>
B46 M4450
Most graduate schools teach students how to survey the scientific literature, identify meaningful scientific questions, and devise experiments to solve the problems.  However, few graduate schools offer formal instruction to help students developing a good sense of historical perspectives and essential on-job skills, which are critical elements for becoming a good scientist.  Successful formulation of critical concepts often results in significant advancement and major paradigm shift in science.  Learning how these specific ideas evolved in a historical context can be quite educational and therefore beneficial to students aspiring to develop a career in sciences.
</>
