102 14202
This course focuses on poetry and the verse form by perusing a wide range of poems in diverse styles and A Midsummer Night’s Dream, a Shakespearean drama in verse form. The basic elements of poetry, such as language, structure, rhyme, and meter, shall be discussed in the context of applicable examples.
