102 21280
課程概述  Course Description
This course aims to provide a comprehensive exposure to advanced English Grammar with a close comparison of British and American usage. The course is most suitable for students with the equivalent level as determined by the Council of Europe level C1 or those at a similar level as students able to write the Cambridge ESOL exams CAE/CPE. The major emphasis is on preparing students for any upcoming competency exams as well as helping those interested in improving their grammar and English usage for their English Composition courses at an undergraduate level.
評量方式  Grading
1. Attendance: 20%
2. Class Participation: 30%
3. Final Examination: 50%
進度  Syllabus
第1週 Present Time; Conditionals.
第2週 Unreal Time and Subjunctives
第3週 Inversion.
第4週 Emphasis.
第5週 Future Time.
第6週 Past Time.
第7週 Present Perfect.
第8週  Reported Speech.
第9週  Articles.
第10週 Relative and Non-Finite Clauses.
第11週 Verbs Plus Infinitive or ing.
第12週 Verbs Plus Preposition.
第13週 Prepositions.
第14週 Phrasal Verbs I
第15週 Phrasal Verbs II
第16週 Phrasal Verbs III; Count Non-Count Nouns
第17週 Modals; Linking Words and Phrases
第18週  （Final Exam）
