102 49132
This year-long course teaches students to write academic research papers, especially for but not limited to those who expect to enter graduate program or go abroad for further study. The second semester focuses on teaching the steps of writing a research paper from scratch, that is, from deciding on a research topic, writing proposals and outlines, gathering and evaluating sources, formatting bibliography, to writing drafts and revision. Students will write a 12-page citing at least 8 outside sources. For the purpose of effective training, the papers have to be on literature-related topics.
