102 50112
How can public speaking be an artistic act? If such act entails a creative process, are there strategies for beginner speakers to convey
ideas not only in a comprehensible manner but
also in an interesting fashion? Before we know how
to speak, we need to learn how to listen. This course,
therefore, develops from the two principles: expressing
your thoughts and understanding other voices.
Throughout the semester, we will explore various forms of
speaking through pair and small-group activities, so
you will test your ability of public speaking in activities
such as role play, impromptu speech and debate, poetry
recital, and group projects.
Participation and attendance are obligatory as part of
your performance will be assessed by other members.
You are expected to form a close rapport with other
classmates because many projects and assignments are
also group-based.
