102 50112
The second part of the course continues the training to hone the students' English communicative skills in order to facilitate effective and accurate speaking. The course will mainly be conducted in small group discussions and activities, ranging from situational conversation, problem solving to verbal games. Class time will be divided into two major segments: first, a lecture on the textbook followed by extended and supervised group discussions and participations.
</>
<c>
102 50112
Oral Training One is designed to enhance each student’s communicative competence in English. Each course build upon the grammatical and lexical competencies the students have already obtained in high school. Fluency in English is fostered by introducing some of the aspects of communicative competence, such as: sociolinguistic competence, discourse competence and strategic competence.
The first year students are taught using a situational/notional/functional approach. These are communicative methods of instruction which are student-centered rather than teacher-centered. These approaches require the students to interact in small group discussions and activities.
</>
