122 M0080
This course introduces students to the thesis writing process. A main focus will be about how to choose and refine a research focus, and write a proposal. In addition, students are encouraged to develop writing habits, and start thesis writing. This seminar depends on intensive peer collaboration. Most sessions are composed of oral presentations and writing workshops. Students are also required to work closely with their academic advisor in this process.
