146 U9090
This is a beginning course in Mandarin, there’s no prerequisite of this course. This class is designed to help students acquire Knowledge of spoken and written Chinese and to assist them in gaining proficiency and accuracy using these skills in real-life situations. The curriculum emphasizes the development of the competency of listening, speaking, reading and writing skills, especially on topics of daily concerns.
