147 M0040
A both practical and theoretical introduction to Chinese-English comparative/contrastive analysis for translators/interpreters. We will begin with sound, from phoneme to syllable to word and phrase, then analyze structure and meaning at the word, phrase, and discursive levels. Then we'll move on to Rhetoric, Stylistics and Register in comparative context. Every time we'll do a sight paragraph warmup!
