202 35000
In this lecture we will cover Python, as the programming basis. Python is an interpreted, general-purpose high-level programming language whose design philosophy emphasizes code readability. Based on this knowledge of Python, we will introduce commonly used numerical methods in scientific computing.
Here are the outline for the course:
Part I: Python
1. the basis
2. Control flow
3. Types and data structure
4. Functions
5. Input
&
Output
6. Modules and classes
Part II: Scientific computing
1. Numerical differential and integration
2. Random numbers
3. Visualization
4. Linear algebra
5. Root finding and minimum finding
6. Differential equations
7. Curve fitting and data modeling
