<c>
204 22600
Taiwan, due to its location and unique geological structure, offers a variety of breath-taking scenery. The Dept. of Geosciences offers an elective course-Introduction to Field Geology (II), which gives a general geological introduction to Heng-Chun Peninsula, Southern Taiwan. It will guide you exploring Taiwan through breath-taking sceneries and magnificent geological features that were made due to the particular location of Taiwan. The course is taught in English and specially designed for international students. All international students, including degree students, exchange students and visiting students, are welcomed to take this course.
</>
