<c>
222 M1420
教科書：R. Shankar, Principles of Quantum Mechanics, 2nd Ed., Plenum Press, New York, 1994.
The course is designed around the lectures. I will be in most cases following the outline but not precisely following the contents of the textbook by Shankar. The material will be a synthesis of the textbook, reference books and my own understanding of the subject. But the outline of the textbook is a pretty good guide to what I expect to cover; the topics are mostly standard and essential.
Course outline：The Hydrogen Atom, Spin, Addition of Angular Momenta, Variational and WKB Methods, Time-Independent Perturbation Theory, Time-Dependent Perturbation Theory, Scattering Theory, and the Dirac Equation。
</>
