<c>
223 M0090
To inspire students to become aware of the current development in the selected Chemistry field by instructing students to read a series of research papers in the selected field, to organize the related knowledge for presentation in a professional manner, to write concise statements about the materials to be presented, and to present and discuss the subject in a seminar format.
</>
<c>
223 M0090
</>
<c>
223 M0090
http://www.ch.ntu.edu.tw/course/course94/studyguide.htm
</>
<c>
223 M0090
http://www.ch.ntu.edu.tw/course/course94/studyguide.htm
</>
<c>
223 M0090
The main purpose of this course is to provide students an opportunity to get acquainted with reading current literature in chemical biology. Emphasis will be placed on gathering the necessary background knowledge, presenting the literature, and providing independent constructive criticism (in a nice way).
</>
<c>
223 M0090
