<c>
223 U0860
This course integrates chemical principles from sophomore- and junior-level courses into lectures on the structure and function of biological molecules. The lectures will emphasize the structural and biological aspects, serving as extensions from the molecular level. The structural portions build on knowledge of the structure and conformation of organic compounds and serve to understand biomolecular function. The biological portion is meant to extend the chemical understanding to biological systems.
</>
