224 D1320
Designed to complement “Advanced stratigraphy”, this course stresses case studies related to modern developments of stratigraphy. The content of the course can be adjusted fit to the students’ requests and will be held in a seminar-type fashion. The students can freely choose the subjects they are interested in and carry out a pilot research. To prepare for the research, the students need to collect relevant references and complete two literature reviews beforehand. The results of literature reviews and the term project will be presented in the class.
