224 U2610
生物地球化學循環和全球環境及氣候變遷之間的聯繫是怎樣的？這種聯繫在地球的歷史中如何變化，將來又會如何影響地球的未來？
What is the link between biogeochemical cycles and global changes in environment and climate? How does it evolve in the earth's history, and how will it shape our future?
</>
<c>
224 U2620
This course is intended for the 3rd-yr and 4th-yr undergraduate students, who is interested in evolution of modern and fossil coral reefs and their relation with global change and paleoclimate. This course will allow students absorbing enough basic and advanced background. It covers topics from coral spawning and symboisis, coral calcification, coral development, Quaternary reef terraces, impact of global warming on coral reef, limestone, carbonate geochemistry and application to earth sciences.  Paper reading, discussion and presentation will play essential roles in class. One 4-day field trip to diverse sites in southern Taiwan will be conducted.
1.	Introduction
2.	Modern coral calcification
3.	Modern coral reef development
4.	Culturing experiment
5.	Quaternary reefs
6.	Microatoll
7.	Terraces and islands
8.	Coral reefs and climate/enrivonment changes
9.	Limestone
10.	On-site 4-day field trip
11.	Report and oral exam
</>
<c>
224 U2630
Major advances in our understanding of the history of life on Earth have resulted from the study of exceptionally well-preserved fossil sites. Study of such sites from around the world and from different periods in geologic time can provide good examples of some ancient ecosystems in the past.
</>
