241 U1280
I. Ten chapters will be covered in this course:
1. Disasters Come with Industrial Civilization
2. Catastrophic Rise in Sea Level
3. Hazardous Ocean Conditions ?El Ni隳
4. Currents and Environment
5. Waves and Coastal Environment
6. Tides and Coastal Environment
7. Estuarine Environment
8. Marine Resources
9. Marine Pollution
10. Mental Purification
II. Classes
1.The first hour of each class will be lectures on marine environment, and
PowerPoint files will be added as visual aides in the second hour. The marine
environment near Taiwan will be the main theme of discussion.
2.Two hours of total class time every semester will be used for discussion.
3.Two hours of office hours every week for questions.
4.Students can post their questions on the website and either the professor or
the teaching assistant will respond promptly to enhance communication.
</>
