323 M4160
This is a seminar course. It shall study papers in the frontier of international trade/industrial organization research. Students are required to read assigned papers and share their comments in the classroom. Through numerous discussions, students shall be familiar with the recent trend of the literature on trade/industrial organization. Students enroll in this course are required to make two presentations during the semester, on topics approved a priori by the instructor. This course will be of particular help to students who are looking for a research topic for their MA or PhD theses.
</>
