203 211D0
The primary goal of this course is to improve students’ qualitative and quantitative knowledge by introducing some basic concepts in analytical chemistry. The textbook is Analytical Chemistry by Christian/Dasgupta/Schug. The teaching materials cover basic analytical concepts, buffers, electrolytes, complexometric titration, electrochemical analysis, spectrochemical analysis (absorption, fluorescence, and chemiluminescence), principles of chromatography, gas chromatography, liquid chromatography, and capillary electrophoresis.
</>
