401 68000
Laboratory medicine includes clinical biochemistry, hematology, serology
&
immunology, microbiology, virology, ECG, clinical microscopy and transfusion medicine. This class covers the core lecture about theory and clinical application of laboratory tests. We hope all students could have basic knowledge and concepts about laboratory medicine in order to apply this knowledge during the internship training.
