422 M4070
Practicing hours at outpatient clinic, operation room and ward are arranged by the Department of Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery at NTUH. The course is to learn the techniques in diagnosis and treatment of diseases in the oral and maxillofacial region. Under the instructions of attending doctors, the students are allowed to perform various minor surgical procedures at outpatient clinic, act as surgical assistants at the operation rooms and are responsible for taking care of inpatients.
</>
