426 D4380
The overall goal of this class is to facilitate research abilities and to help doctoral students in developing their own research. Each student will present in the class an overview of their recent work on one interested topic, critique methodology of previous research, identify gap in the literature, and propose a research idea to fill the gap. Moreover, it is required for students to present their study in English in order to enhance their ability to conduct an oral presentation in international conferences.
</>
