426 M1100
This course is designed to provide a foundation in nursing research for use in clinical practice and the research settings. Basic concepts and principles of research methodology and process are covered in the lecture component. Emphasis is given on the systematic examination and application of the research process. The concept of evidenced-based practice and its application to nursing is stressed and critically examined.
