<c>
441 M2600
This course is intended for further in-depth study of the gastrointestinal physiology and immunology. The lymphoid tissues in the gastrointestinal tract contain the largest number of immune cells in the body, termed gut-associated lymphoid tissue (GALT). The gastrointestinal tract serves as a first line defense system against potential pathogens and antigens in ingested foods. At the same time, the gastrointestinal tract has to provide oral tolerance to food proteins without developing an immune reaction against exogenous particles. The balance between tolerance and immunity in the gut plays a crucial role in the pathogenesis of various gastrointestinal diseases.
</>
<c>
441 M2900
TO UNDERSTAND THE PHYSIOLOGY OF CARDIOVASCULAR SYSTEM IN HEALTH AND DISEASE STATE THROUGH JOURNAL READING AND DISCUSSION. THIS INCLUDES THE HORMONAL REGULATION, NERVE CONTROL, ION TRANSPORTING AND MECHANORECEPTOR FUNCTION ETC. IN CARDIOVASCULAR SYSTEM. THE CONSEQUENCES OF HEMODYNAMIC CHANGE, ELECTRIC DISORDER AND MYOCARDIAL ISCHEMIA ETC. WILL BE EMPHASIZED IN THE COURSE.
</>
