449 M1300
EXAMINATION OF THE BASIC PRINCIPLES AND APPLICATIONS IN MEDICAL DISEASES AND DEVELOPMENT OF MEDICINE AND BIOTECHNOLOGY PRODUCTS. THESE CONTENTS WILL LAY THE FOUNDATION FOR IMMUNE MECHANISMS IN CLINICAL DISEASES, TREATMENTS AND BIOTECHNOLOGY INTERVENTIONS. FOR EACH CLASS, THE FOUR MAJOR PARTS TO BE ADDRESSED ARE: (1) ETIOLOGY (CAUSE OF THE DISEASE) AND DISEASE TARGET; (2) PATHOGENESIS, (3) MEDICAL APPLICATIONS AND TREATMENTS, AND (4) BIOTECHNOLOGY AND PRODUCT DESIGN.
