453 D0150
This course is designed to be an introductory course for those who are interested in understanding oncogenesis. The course will cover several issues including epigenetics, tumor angiogenesis, immunosurveillance, immune escape and inflammation in the process of malignant transformation. Some materials, like cell cycle and chemical carcinogenesis, will not be explained in full detail but will be reviewed briefly. Those who have taken one basic course in tumor biology and graduate students from non-oncology backgrounds are welcome.
</>
