501 39980
In the course of water supply and sewerage, the students learn the subjects of water supply engineering (including collection, transport, treatment and distribution) and sewerage work engineering (including sewer and storm systems). Water and wastewater treatment processes are only introduced in water supply and sewerage. Therefore, the theory and practice of water and wastewater treatment are the main topics in the course of engineered systems for water and sewage treatment (environmental engineering (II)).
