521 M5230
This advanced course introduces fundamental mechanics of sediment transport. After students have a basic understanding of sediment transport modeling, we will present several probability theories and models that can be used to describe the stochastic behavior of sediment particles under uncertainty.
In class, we will discuss 6-8 representative journal papers.  Students are asked to present their report on selected journal papers in class
