527 U3150
Course Objective: This course is designed to provide students, both graduate and senior undergraduate, in-depth understanding of the concepts of quantum chemistry that are important to the discipline of materials science and engineering.
Textbooks:
1. I. N. Levine, “Quantum Chemistry”
2. P. Atkins, J. de Paula, “Physical Chemistry”
3. T. Engel, P. Reid, “Physical Chemistry”
4. D. A. McQuarrie, J. D. Simon, “Physical Chemistry: A Molecular Approach”
Course outline:
1. Basic quantum theory
–	the quantum mechanical postulate
–	the Schrodinger equation
–	particle in a box
–	harmonic oscillator
–	rigid rotor
2. Atomic structure and spectra
–	single-electron atoms
–	multi-electron atoms – methods of approximation
variation
perturbation
3. Molecular structure
–	diatomic molecules
–	polyatomic molecules – approximation techniques and computational chemistry
4. Molecular symmetry
5. Photo-Physical Processes and Spectroscopy
–	vibrational and rotational spectroscopy
–	electronic spectroscopy
–	NMR
