541 D1140
Advanced Environmental Microbiology
A two-credit microbiology course is designed for doctoral student in environmental engineering or related field. This course will be comprised with lectures, discussion sessions, and essay writing. The goals of this course are to provide an overall view of microbial ecology, address biological engineering processes with microbial perspectives, and writing skills challenge. The detailed outlines are listed below.
1.	Significance and challenges of environmental microbiology
2.	Key biogeochemical and evolutionary events
3.	Microbial diversity
4.	Microbial ecology
5.	Generating and interpreting information in environmental microbiology: methods and limitations
6.	Microbial biogeography
7.	Applied topics in environmental microbiology
a.	Water, wastewater, soil bioremediation
b.	Evolution of organic metabolic pathways
Grading system:
Articles review and discussion: 50%
Essay writing: 50%
</>
