543 M1110
THIS IS THE FIRST COURSE IN NUMERICAL ANALYSIS FOR GRADUATE STUDENTS. THE MAIN OBJECTIVES OF THIS COURSE INCLUDE:
(1)	DEVELOPMENT AND APPLICATIONS OF NUMERICAL METHODS WHEN ANALYTICAL TECHNIQUES ARE NOT AVAILABLE;
(2)	DEVELOPMENT OF A CONCEPTUAL FRAMEWORK FOR ANALYSIS OF METHODS TO FIX THE PROBLEM;
(3)	DISCRETE CALCULUS AND APPROXIMATIONS;
(4)	TRADEOFFS BETWEEN ACCURACY AND COMPUTATIONAL COST;
