543 M4730
This is an introductory course in the basic theory of electromagnetics for students in the engineering school. The main topics include electrostatics, magnetostatics, and electrodynamics, which cover the basic principles such as Coulomb's law, Gauss's law, Biot-Savart's law, Ampere's law, Faradya's law, and Maxwell's equations.
</>
