543 M6110
Course contents:
(1) Introduction (6 hours)
(2) Physical and mathematical formulations of fluid mechanics (11 hours)
(3) Some exact solutions for illustrating various terms of the equations (6 hours)
(4) The flow physics from small to large Reynolds numbers (3 hours)
(5) Low Reynolds number flows (5 hours)
(6) Potential flows (6 hours)
(7) Laminar boundary layer theory (6 hours)
(8) General discussion on other topics in fluid mechanics (5 hours)
The contents of the course are similar to those of the fluid mechanics courses for the first year graduate students of most universities throughout the world
