548 M0552
A major challenge in biomedical engineering is the immense scope of biomedically relevant problems, which range from the molecular scale to the macroscopic scale. Bioengineering problems can be effectively treated through the use of the modeling techniques and mathematical tools. Therefore, mathematics is the basic requirements in biomedical engineering.
