621 D1320
This module is meant to be a place for analysis, discussion, criticism and brainstorming around a selection of diverse topics related to breeding. In addition to conventional course presentation given by the course leader, students will be asked to lead some topics, either suggested by the course leader or by students themselves. Topics below will be presented in the module:
1. Application of molecular markers in breeding
2. Genomic prediction
3. Genotype x Environment interaction: multi-environment trials
4. Breeding – industry perspective
5. Participatory plant breeding
6. Crop wild relatives
