621 U6440
本課程講授稻之起源、形態及品種特性、生育環境、稻之栽培制度、稻之栽培法、稻米生產、稻米品質及生物技術等。
</>
<c>
621 U6450
Genome science has been one of the most blooming sciences in the past decade. The complete genome sequences of the dicot model plant, Arabidopsis, and of the monocot crops such as rice, sorghum and maize are released. In addition, many crops and plants are undergone sequencing. The genomic information provides various research methodologies and speeds up traditional researches. This course will emphasize on genetic mapping, physical mapping, and genome sequencing and annotating to dissect plant genomes. Consequently, this course will introduce the applications of genomics in positional cloning, gene expression, comparative mapping, genetic variation and so on.
</>
<c>
621 U6660
綠色產業是在全球氣候變遷現象明顯而被社會大眾認知之後，為了減緩氣候變遷速度及彌補其所產生的效應所採取的一些相關措施之後，而發展出來的一系列的作法，這些做法累積之後便蛻變形成新的產業，就是所謂的綠色產業。本課程將就氣候變遷形成的原因進行討論，將生態系統解析成為水，能源，碳及氮循環等四大循環系統，說明及探討與現代氣候變遷的關係。接著對地球上人類生存所依賴的資源分為生物性與非生物性兩類並包括土地資源進行說明與探討。接著就由食，衣，住，行與居住等五方面分別說明永續性發展的現況與發展方向，並討論現階段針對大氣溫室氣體排放處理的議題，包括碳排放的估算，減少排放與實質的減量作為。最後就由士農工商與教育等五大領域提出現行的發展現況與未來的方向。
</>
<c>
621 U6680
The specialty chocolate processing and sensory evaluation skill will be introduced and practiced in depth in this course.  The raw cocoa bean from the world production areas will be used during the course for sensory evaluation samples preparation.
The spices, sweeteners, and other ingredients will be included during the process. And the roasting of the raw cocoa bean and the control of the texture through grinding will also be sampled to be included in the sensory evaluation.  The student is expected to be able to distinguish the differences by the processing through sensory evaluation.
</>
