627 D1720
This course provides a graduate sequence in applied econometrics that is suitable for Ph.D. students. I plan to cover linear regression models and the associated estimation and testing procedure. In addition, the course introduces some more advanced topics. This is an applied econometrics course with an extensive "hands-on" approach. Theory will be studied in order to be able to develop skills for applied work only. Computer exercises and applications to the real world problems will be emphasized.
