629 M1212
Since this is an advanced course of poultry diseases. Discussion as well as lecture are given during the course. This is for the students to understand the true meaning of a disease, which include
1.	pathogenesis of poultry agents, i.e. Newcastle disease, avian influenza. The relationship between virulence and the sequences of some important viruses are given in this course.
2.	published papers in Avian Diseases and Avian Pathology, and other related journals.
3.	question discussion for the board exam from AAAP.
4. Every odd Monday from 13:20 to 15:10
