630 M3240
In this seminar, we will review ways in which social scientists have incorporated concepts about space, place, and distance into their theories and research. Examples will be drawn from many substantive areas. Class meetings will be organized around the course readings. Classes will operate as a seminar in which every reading is introduced orally by one student (*who is expected to prepare 1-2 page written summaries for distribution). Your participation in these presentations and discussions will count 20% of your course grade.
