633 M1482
In my laboratory, we use
molecular biology,
biochemistry and cell
biology to resolve the
signal transduction pathway
inside of cells in response
to specific extracelluar
stimuli. By manupilating the
signal molecules invovled in
the signaling pathways, it
enables us to characterize
the role of a specific
pathway or molecules. Our
research is focusing on the
kinases and the associated
pathways which are key in
cell migration and cell
proliferation. The further
implication will orient
toward tumor metastasis
mediated by these kinases
and signaling pathways.
</>
