642 D0060
COURSE OUTLINES AS FOLLOWING:
PART I : TRANSGENIC ANIMALS
1. INTRODUCTION OF TRANSGENIC ANIMALS
2. GENERATION OF TRANSGENIC ANIMALS
3. FACTORS OF AFFECTING TRANSGENIC ANIMAL PRODUCTION
4. TRANSGENIC ANIMAL MODEL SYSTEM
5. APPLICATIONS OF TRANSGENIC FARM ANIMALS
PART II: SOMATIC CELL NUCLEAR TRANSFER (SCNT) IN ANIMAL
6. AN OVERVIEW OF STRATEGIES TO INDUCE EPIGENETIC REPROGRAMMING
7. INTRODUCTION OF NUCLEAR REPROGRAMMING BY SOMATIC CELL NUCLEAR TRANSFER
8. SOMATIC NUCLEAR TRANSFER IN RODENT SPECIES
9. SOMATIC NUCLEAR TRANSFER IN DOMESTIC ANIMAL SPECIES
10. INTERSPECIES NUCLEAR TRANSFER (INT) AND ITS IMPLICATIONS FOR EMBRYONIC STEM CELL BIOLOGY
11. EPIGENETIC REGULATION IN CLONED EMBRYO DEVELOPMENT
12. DERIVATION AND CHARACTERIZATION OF ESCS FROM CLONED EMBRYOS
13. APPLICATIONS OF CLONING, REPRODUCTIVE VS. THERAPEUTIC CLONING
14. ETHICAL CONCERNS OF ANIMAL CLONING AND EMBRYONIC STEM RESEARCH
