The primary goal of this course is to familiarize students with econometric
analysis of cross session and panel data. We will also discuss the
identification problem. There is no formal prerequisite. However, you are
expected to have known the basic asymptotic theories, such as the Law of Large
Numbers and the Central Limit Theorem.
We will use  Identification Problems in the Social Sciences  by Charles F. Manski (Harvard University Press 1995) to introduce the identification problem.
