<c>
704 11400
We are moving toward a world in which trade
&
investment barriers are declining; perceived distance is shrinking due to advances in transportation
&
telecommunication technology; cultural differences are converging and economies are merging into independent, integrated global economic system. The globalization has created both opportunities and threats for businesses accustomed to operating merely in their home markets.
Given we have witnessed the globalization of markets and production, this course aims to look at how the nature of international business is changing in response to the changing global economy; we are to discuss important issues raised by rapid globalization; and we will review implications of rapid globalization for individual managers.
</>
<c>
704 20112
在現代經濟和社會結構愈趨複雜之際，大至國家小至個人之決策行為，對資料分析之依賴日甚，僅憑經驗或常識已不足以應付千變萬化的實際事務。因此客觀分析實為非常重要的工作，尤其瞭解統計理論對一般人之重要性日漸增高。本課程之內容包括敘述統計與推論統計，課程之目的在於介紹統計觀念及各種實用統計方法以解決實際需要。為能有效處理及分析資料，統計套裝軟體的操作是研究者不可或缺的能力，本課程講授的統計套裝軟體以 SPSS 及 EXCEL 為主。
</>
<c>
704 20112
統計學(Statistics)給人的刻板印象往往是要背一大堆艱澀難懂的數學公式，或是要處理一堆雜亂無章的數據資料，因此讓不少學生對統計學心生卻步。事實上，統計學正是要利用這些看似難懂的數學公式，來消化那些龐大的原始資料，運用科學的方法，協助我們在龐大的資料中萃取出有用的資訊，以便我們做出有科學依據的正確決策。現代統計學運用範圍很廣，舉凡農業(農產統計、農業指標)、工業(作業管理、工廠品管)、商業(金融服務、國際貿易、企業管理)、或是其他自然科學(數學、物理)、社會科學(政治、教育)，都與統計學息息相關。統計學好比一把鑰匙(一項工具)，便利我們更有效地去探索其他有趣的領域。在基礎的統計學中，我們將學習運用Excel來處理資料，解決問題。
</>
<c>
704 20600
The course is designed to help the students learn the basic concepts of modern marketing in a management-orientation way. The most basic objectives of this course are to provide you with a broad introduction to marketing concepts, the role of marketing in society and in the firm, and the various factors that influence marketing decision-making.
Like other IB courses, you will be expected to familiarize with the ‘language of marketing’ (i.e., terms, concepts, and frameworks) used by practicing marketing managers, and have a solid understanding of the major decision area under marketing responsibility. It focuses on major decisions that marketing manager faces in their efforts to harmonize the objectives and resources of the organization with the needs and opportunities in the marketplace. Within time limits, this class attempts to cover all the topics that a marketing manager needs to face in strategic, tactical, and administrative marketing.
</>
