704 30800
This course examines the challenges of entering and operating effectively in foreign markets. Decisions must be made regarding international marketing objectives, strategies and policies, foreign market selection, adaptation of products, distribution channels and communications to fit each foreign market, and systems of international marketing organization, information gathering, planning and control. These topics, along with exploration of cultural issues, are examined through reading, case discussion, class presentations and a team project. It covers the main issues faced in strategic, tactical, and administrative international marketing.
</>
<c>
704 32600
本課程將依序講授包含跨國企業與財務管理的介紹、外匯市場與匯率風險管理、國際投資決策、國際融資決策及國際營運資金管理等主題，並輔以時事資料及個人經驗分享作為補充，同時，在學期中將邀請兩位相關領域的專家，分享實務經驗。個案的安排上，將以「Prada: To IPO or Not to IPO: That is the Question, Again」為第一個個案，另將安排三個個案供同學直接於課堂上閱讀、分析及討論〈每組四至六人〉，此外，學期末將以五家上市、櫃公司〈王品、誠品生、網家、聯發科、台積電〉之真實案例作為同學研究主題，期待同學經過完整課程訓練後，具備實務分析能力。最後，本學期也將安排一次學期考試，以檢定同學的學習成效。
</>
<c>
704 32700
The objective of this course is to give students an overview of major theories, debates, and empirical results in international finance. We will focus on the following topics: currency exchange rates, exchange rate regimes, foreign exchange parity relations, foreign exchange determination and forecasting, balance of payments, and global capital markets. Although these topics may be highly mathematical, we will quickly review the technical parts and emphasize the concepts and intuitions of them.
</>
