<c>
722 M1000
Traditional management accounting has lost its relevance in the current competitive business environment. This course will provide the students with some insights into how to restore the relevance of management accounting in the overall success of organization. How management accounting can facilitate managerial decision-making and influence employees and managers’ behavior will be the focus of this course. We will also discuss the linkage of management ac-counting with the firm’s strategy so that management accounting can be used to improve the firm’s competitive advantages.
</>
