848 M2300
本課程旨在不僅幫助同學熟悉專案管理理論，而且能學會使用Microsoft Project軟體。最後，就是期望同學能應用專案管理於實務中，以改善專案績效。
The purpose of this course is not only to help students become familiar with the project management theories, but also to be able to learn to use Microsoft Project software. Finally, it is expected that students can apply project management into practices to improve project performance.
</>
<c>
848 M2310
發展多樣化、跨領域整合的長期照護體系以因應急速增加的老年族群照護需求是已開發國家的普遍目標。本課程經由授課與討論來探討國際長期照護體系的經驗，進而探討台灣目前與未來長期照護體系的發展。本課程期望透過國際不同類型的長期照護服務體系介紹與優缺利弊的探討，培養學生對國內長照現況與問題的瞭解與對未來台灣長期照護體系與產業發展的空間想像，進而拓展學生對台灣長期照護體系發展的視野與經營管理的能力。課程分為兩大部分:
Part I: 介紹國際不同長期照護服務體系並討論優缺點
Part II: 介紹國內長期照護體系目前與未來發展
Developing diverse and integrated long-term care services to meet care demands for the rapidly increasing older population is a common goal for many developed countries in the world. This course will explore experiences of long-term care in Western countries and then apply the lessons learned to current long-term care service development in Taiwan. Students will be introduced to available knowledge in the field of long-term care service development, effective problem-solving attitudes, and techniques for organizing information and/or developing management strategies in the field. This course included two parts:
Part I: Introduction and discussion of international experiences with long-term care services
Part II: Introduction and discussion of Taiwan’s current and future development of long-term care services
</>
<c>
848 M2340
隨著科技不斷進步，人口老化加快，醫療費用上升，醫療品質要求提高，醫療機構持續引進各論理論，來因應此生態的改變。醫院資訊化，是一精簡有效率的一種方式，但如何讓醫院同仁接納不產生抗拒，與管理階層能相輔相成，是本課程所需要探討的目標。
Since the advancement of the technology and the incensement of aged persons, health service fees and service quality, hospital institute continuously incorporates a variety of theory and practice to struggle for the change of the healthcare environment. That the hospital introduces the information technology is an efficient way, but it encounters the resistance of staff and doctors. How to seamlessly introduce the information technology and aid the management smoothly is the topic of this course.
</>
<c>
848 M2380
本課程由美國南加大 Prof. Robert Myrtle 講授，全英文授課
Rapidly changing global environments, health care policy and competitive forces in an increasingly boundaryless health care delivery system demand transformative and visionary leaders. This course is designed to provide current and future health care executives with the intellectually frameworks, contemporary theory and applications to respond effectively to these dynamic changes. Building on concepts from psychology, sociology and the behavioral sciences this course will prepare students to develop the capacity to develop, lead and transform health care organizations and the institutional networks that embody the health care delivery system. Contemporary theory suggests that the development of highly effective, transformative leaders emerges from a framework that combines self assessment and reflection embedded in the constructs of emotional intelligence, with theories and methods designed to provide the participants the latest thoughts associated with leading, individuals, teams, organizations and interorganizational networks.
</>
