848 U0010
The course adopts an interactive approach to language learning by providing you with ample opportunities to “interact” with your instructor, your classmates, and, most importantly, with the writer in you.  Major class activities include: (1). Group discussions; (2). Peer reviews; (3). Guided exercises and editing; and (4). Required writing assignments in various forms (self-introduction, process, cause-effect, comparison-contrast, classification, argumentative paragraphs/essays) culminating in four to five fully revised papers the entire semester.
</>
<c>
848 U1060
本課程旨在介紹如何運用個體經濟學的原理來分析健康照護市場的供需行為。課程首先會簡要回顧個體經濟學原理的概要，再進入健康照護市場的分析，包括對健康與醫療服務需求以及相關的影響因素、醫師與醫院的供給行為分析、健康保險的支付設計與財源、以及我國全民健保與改革等。本課程係一導論性之設計，也歡迎沒有接觸過經濟學的同學選修。透過理論的講解與實務問題的討論，使同學對健康經濟學的理論與應用以及台灣的醫療照護市場有進一步的了解。
This course intends to introduce the basic theory of microeconomics and its application to analyze the supply and demand in health care market. This course starts with a brief review of the essences of microeconomics. Analysis on health care market includes demand for health and health care, factors associated with the demands, physician and hospitals in the market, demand for health insurance, financial incentives and supplier behavior, and health care reform etc. This is an introductory course; students without any economic knowledge are welcome. Via lecture and discussion, this course intends to enhance students’ understanding of health economics as well as the health care system in Taiwan.
</>
