849 M0030
流行病學實例研究 (碩班)、流行病學實例研究一 (博一)、流行病學實例研究二 (博二)
本課程透過閱讀、報告與討論教師指定的原著論文，建立學生對於文獻具批判性的深入瞭解，增進知識深度，另外也透過接觸不同領域研究的最新進展增進知識廣度，了解全球大趨勢。每位碩班同學需口頭報告二次，訓練深度閱讀及條理清晰、要點凸顯和台風穩健的學術表達能力。所要報告的論文在第一循環是由指導教師指定，第二循環則以隨機抽籤方式決定（不同領域論文優先，如已無不同領域論文則抽籤非自己指導教授提供之選讀論文）。碩班同學報告時間三人報告時為25分鐘，四人報告時則為18分鐘，然後由博班同學評論報告內容，評論及討論時間為10-15分鐘。每位博班同學上台辯論1次，辯論題目由同學諮詢指導老師後自行選定，以能夠引發熱烈討論的題目較佳。辯論目的在培養同學就事論事，憑證據說話的素養，以科學求真求實態度透明檢驗一個議題的正反觀點。正反方報告各 25分鐘，提問及回答各約 10-15 分鐘。三人組：一人主持辯論及做Introduction與最後conclusion，正反方各一人。四人組：一人主持及做Introduction，正反方各一人，第四人做結論。
關於語言：
本課程鼓勵同學報告及評論時使用英語，但不強制。如果無法用英語充分表達，可以使用國語。是否使用英語不影響成績評定。
This course requires students to read, present, and comment on research papers designated by teachers. This course aims to help the students to build up the competency to read scientific literature, and to participate the discussion on the latest advances reported by global scientific communities. Each Master student presents twice. The first paper will be assigned by his/her advisor, and the second paper will be randomly assigned. The time for each presentation is 25 minutes (3-student session) or 18 minutes (4-students session). PhD students make comments on papers presented by Master students. The time for comment and group discussion is 10-15 minutes. Each PhD student participates debate once. The subject of debate is chosen by the students after consulting the advisor. The purpose of the debate is to help students to master the skill to examine the pros and cons of a subject from scientific evidence. Both sides have 25 minutes for main presentation, 10-15 minutes for questions and answers. For a 3-person group, student A introduces the subject and makes the conclusion remark, student B advocates the affirmative view, and student C advocates the opposite view. For a 4-person group, student A introduces the subject, student B advocates the affirmative view, and student C advocates the opposite view, and student D makes the conclusion remark.
About Language:
This course encourages students to use English in presentation, comment, and discussion, but students can use Chinese whenever necessary. The choice of language will not affect the final evaluation.
</>
