901 39800
LECTURES: INTRODUCTION TO COMMUNICATION THEORY AND SIMULATION :
- DIGITAL MODULATION
- LINEAR BLOCK CODE
- CONVOLUTIONAL CODED SYSTEMS
- OFDM
- PHASE LOCK LOOP
- SIMULATION BASICS AND CONCEPTS
- MATLAB SIMULINK
- FPGA
- PRESENTATION SKILLS
- PROJECT MANAGEMENT TECHNIQUES
- MISCELLANEOUS
LABS: GIVE PRACTICES WITH THE SOFTWARE AND HARDWARE. ESTABLISH A STARTING POINT FOR PROJECTS. LAB CODE FREQUENTLY SERVES AS STARTING POINT FOR PROJECTS.
SOFTWARE SIMULATIONS OF COMMUNICATIONS SYSTEMS:
- MODULATION ONLY: BPSK, ASK, 8PSK, 16QAM
- CODING + MODULATION: HAMMING CODED SYSTEM, CONVOLUTIONAL CODED SYSTEM
- WIRELESS IMAGE TRANSMISSION
- WIRELESS AUDIO TRANSMISSION
- OFDM (OPTIONAL)
- CODING + MODULATION + OFDM (OPTIONAL)
HARDWARE IMPLEMENTATION:
- ALL DIGITAL PLL
MIDTERM REPORT: EACH GROUP OF 3 STUDENTS CHOOSE A MODERN (ADVANCE) COMMUNICATION SYSTEM (TECHNOLOGY). STUDY, RESEARCH, AND PRESENT TO THE CLASS. EVERYONE CAN HAVE AN OVERVIEW OF 8~10 MODERN COMMUNICATION TECHNOLOGIES BY PARTICIPATING THE PRESENTATIONS. TOPICS INCLUDES:
- WIMEDIA (UWB)
- WIRELESS SENSOR NETWORKS (IEEE 802.15.4, ZIGBEE)
- IEEE 802.15.3C (60GHZ)
- BLUETOOTH
- WIMAX (802.16D, 16J, 16M)
- MOBILE WIMAX (802.16E)
- IEEE 802.11N
- IEEE 802.20
- IEEE 802.21
- IEEE 802.22
- WCDMA
- CDMA2000
- GSM、GPRS、EDGE
- SPREAD SPECTRUM COMMUNICATIONS
- MULTI INPUT MULTI OUTPUT (MIMO)
- ETC.
FINAL PROJECTS: STUDENT SELECTED AND IMPLEMENTED. EITHER SOFTWARE IMPLEMENTATION OF A PREVIOUS STUDIED COMMUNICATION SYSTEM, OR PARTIAL IMPLEMENTATION OF THE SYSTEM BY HARDWARE (FPGA,DSPPROCESSOR,ETC.).
