922 U3130
This is an elective course intended for senior undergraduates and graduate students.
This course covers important concepts in computer security. We will discuss a variety of attack and defense techniques for networking protocols, web, and systems. Topics include DoS/DDoS attack and defense, secure routing, traffic monitoring, anonymity and privacy, censorship resilience, botnet and virus, and usability.
