&
quasi-phase-matching, second harmonic generation, optical parametric amplification and oscillation, Gaussian beam and geometric optics, ABCD matrix and resonator design
Properties of light in matters
Wave propagation in anisotropic (uniaxial, biaxial) crystals), Jones Matrix Formulation of polarized light and optical components,
Nonlinear wave interactions between light and matter
classical anharmonic oscillator model of nonlinear susceptibility
&
nonlinear phenomena, contraction and crystal symmetry, wave equation description of nonlinear optical interactions, phase matching in uniaxial
&
biaxial crystals
Nonlinear optics process for laser generation
quasi-phase-matching, second harmonic generation, optical parametric amplification and oscillation,
