A21 U5110
This course presents the fundamental ideas, achievements, and legislative impacts of the international disability rights movement. The United Nations Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities (UN CRPD), the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA), and relevant caselaw will be discussed in-depth.
</>
