101 80002
Since this course will be offered in the Law School and Sociology School, the materials are selected to reflect the interests of participants, including sections dealing with scholarship, together with government, society, law and economics. Where appropriate, we will include related scholarly papers.
Class Method: A combination of lecture and discussion.
Grading: Based equally on class participation and the final exam. Class participation will be evaluated based on three reports, each of which has equal weight.
