102 83030
This integrated language course aims to enhance students’ English proficiency at the high-intermediate level. The course is also intended to develop in the students an interest in learning English and a more thorough understanding of the English and American culture, as well as to improve students’ critical thinking and presentation skills. In addition to sharpening the students’ English skills, after taking this course, students are expected to become critical readers and thinkers, clear communicators in multiple contexts, and active analysts of contemporary cultures.
*The syllabus might be updated so please check back at least once before the first class.
*A detailed list of readings/clips will be provided in the first class.
</>
<c>
102 83030
This English course focuses on reading and discussion; its main objective consists in cultivating students’ sophisticated and critical thinking on cultural topics. This course will be run mostly in all-English way, with the aim to engage students in intellectual, critical discussions in English. Therefore, students who expect and need concentrated training on practical skills, such as real-life conversation, are not recommended to take this course. Mandarin will be used when complex concepts need to be clarified. The reading material pertains to various genres, including poetry, fiction, critical essay, and film. The issues to be explored include (1) love, (2) virtual relationship, (3) domination and the Holocaust, and (4) religion. Students are required to commit themselves to (1) close reading to acquire a deeper understanding of the text, and (2) continuous collaboration through teamwork and group discussion in order to test and substantiate their grasp of the issue concerned. In general, the objectives to be achieved include the following: (1) to introduce cultural topics which preoccupy the present intellectual world; (2) to enhance students’ critical and sophisticated thinking; (3) to enhance students’ ability to discuss and write on complex, intellectual issues in English. The requirements for students include: (1) interest in thinking; (2) class attendance and active participation; (3) class activities and exercises; (4) close teamwork.
</>
<c>
102 83030
本課程旨在墊立並厚實同學日後獨立學習英文之基礎，以閱讀分析之訓練為主，聽講與口語練習為輔，間有文法習作。同學必須積極主動參與教學，不厭其煩地進行閱讀之預習與其他相關操練方能符合課程要求。閱讀訓練分課堂細讀與課外泛讀二類，課堂閱讀主題單元包括：建立成就動機、認識閱讀過程、掌握閱讀技巧、培養分析推理以及訓練批判閱讀等。教材涵蓋人文、藝術、社會、自然科學、新聞報導等不同類型之文章，每學期並精讀二至三篇短篇小說；取材不以趣味為考量，畢竟何為趣味因人、因時而異。同學可依興趣與喜好擇定課外閱讀材料，並繳交閱讀報告。上課主要以英文進行，以增進學生聽講能力。同學必須就分配之文章分組報告，彼此提問，就各種可能的閱讀疑難進行討論；在過程中反覆操練發現問題、了解問題，並學習解決問題的方法與途徑。聽講練習題材與方式不拘，包括日常會話、新聞報導、演講與聽寫；口語訓練要求同學必須練習以英文陳述生活經驗或感想，並將閱讀中習得之詞彙與知識應用於相關主題之討論。
</>
<c>
102 83030
This section of Freshman English is designed as an interactive and student-centered workshop to help students improve their listening, speaking, reading and writing abilities in English through various activities and exposure to a wide variety of materials in English. Using resources such as English interviews, news videos, newspaper and magazine articles, and intriguing talks on the Internet, we will focus on issues in the contemporary world. Students are expected to spend two to four hours a week to prepare for class, probably including reading an article, listening to an interview, or watching a video, in order to equip themselves with necessary knowledge and vocabulary for class discussion. In class, the topic of the week will be further explored through group presentations. We will have Writing workshop, Speech workshop, and Reading workshop in this semester. Finally, students need to give a 5-minute speech and a group presentation (60 minutes, including 10-minute/15-minute group discussions).
</>
<c>
102 83030
The primary purpose of this course is to improve students’ proficiency of English through reading, writing, listening, and oral practices. In order to prepare students for further academic pursuits or advanced English studies, various types of reading materials will be included in the course, especially articles related to major cultural practices and issues, such as race, gender, class, and pop culture. In other words, this is a course which not only purports to improve students’ English capability but also aims to achieve that objective by cultivating their sensitivity to important cultural issues. Students of the class will be divided into groups and discuss questions developed from the reading material in English, and after the discussion, one member of the group has to present the conclusion to the whole class in English. As for listening practices, each week one or two latest video clips from CNN will be broadcasted in class to which students will have to answer questions prepared by the instructor. In addition, 3 short summaries of the reading materials are required.
</>
