141 10300
Generally Southeast Asian culture possible to see as various kinds of historical complex such as the local pre-historical, Indian, Chinese, Islamic and European influenced cultures.  In this process several religions were acted very important role for formation of such cultural diversity and basic similarity in this area.  Also geological separation between the Continent and the Archipelago involves the whole complex situation.  In this course I will show a total historical cultural changes with point of view of religion for each arts; architecture, sculpture, ceramic, textile, performing arts (including dance and music) and archaeological remains.
