<c>
102 22320
Course Description
The goal of this course is to foster and to improve students’ Spanish interaction overcoming the students’ difficulties to express in an oral interaction. In this respect, the course will be a way of consolidating/achieving A2 level of Common European Framework of Reference (CEFR), that is, students become Waystage users.
進度 Syllabus
第1週 Introductions, greetings, farewells and ask personal information.
第2週 Describe the house: ask and answer quantities, locate furniture and items.
第3週 Move in the city: ask for the existence of a place, locate a place, ask address, explain how to arrive there, ask time and ask timetables / schedules.
第4週 Look for Mr/Mrs Right: describe yourself and other people (physical and psychological description); talk about your routines; talk about likes/dislikes.
第5週 Eat at the restaurant: express desires, order a meal, ask prices, express likes and dislikes, ask someone for doing something.
第6週 Go shopping and do the shop: express your preferences; ask permanent and non-permanent prices; describe the traits of the item you want (color, size, shape…) and bargain over; compare/contrast prices.
第7週 Invitations: Invite, propose or arrange an appointment; accept or refuse proposals; express duties/obligations; convince someone about our proposals.
第8週 Go on a trip in the city/outside the city: propose plans; propose alternatives; get a consensus; express lack of interest; express probability, doubt or uncertainty; phone institutions (agencies, companies, cinemas…) for asking information (prices, conditions…)
第9週 期中考
第10週 Travel abroad: ask information about means of transportations (fares, conditions…); compare offers; ask information about accommodation; ask information about touristic places/ places o interest; activities to do during the journey…
第11週 Become a cook: give instructions; express possibilities; express personal and impersonal prohibitions; express real conditions.
第12週 Go to the doctor: explain symptoms; give advices; propose
</>
