102 83220
本課程旨在增進學生聽說讀寫四方面技能整合性之運用以及培養學生自主與合作學習的能力。教學方式以啟發學生自我學習為主，在教師協助下，配合視聽教材及電腦網路資源的運用，安排學生，或個人或小組，加強聽講、會話、閱讀和寫作之練習，並佐以學習策略之訓練。
英語的學習應不僅限於學校課堂裡，因此本課程為培養學生自主性學習，將輔導學生自行規畫課內外之語言學習，於學期末完成個人學習歷程檔案。
</>
<c>
102 83220
Freshman English (with lab)
Professor Karen Steffen Chung 史嘉琳老師
For more information on this course, please visit:
http://homepage.ntu.edu.tw/~karchung/
Course description:
This course will concentrate on four main areas:
(1) literary appreciation and pronunciation correction through poetry and prose reading, memorization and recitation;
(2) reading and translation practice with essays and short stories;
(3) listening practice with audio and video files on the Internet;
(4) various oral presentations; and possibly:
(5) a few short Chinese-to-English translation practices, to strengthen grammatical skills.
Only serious students who did
well in English in high school and who genuinely enjoy English should choose this course; be forewarned that this is one of the more difficult and tiring Freshman English options, and a fair amount of homework will be assigned. Active class participation is expected of each student in this course.
Course requirements/grade calculation:
Attendance (any student with more than three unexcused absences or five tardinesses may not receive a grade for this course), homework, quizzes, class participation, oral presentations, attitude, progress made, final exam.
No textbook is assigned; students must print out all handouts themselves from the class website; students are also required to bring a small notebook to each class for use as a pronunciation and grammar journal; also a clear pocket folder to organize handouts and homework assignments.
</>
