<c>
102 83420
The purpose of this course is twofold: (1) to further improve your listening, speaking, reading and writing abilities in English, with special emphasis on listening fluency and comprehension development, and (2) to help you develop academic skills that can help you transit successfully from high school to university classes.  To achieve these goals, you need to work both in and out of class. You need to complete the assigned reading before class and participate actively in class discussions, group exercises and on-line learning. You also need to complete a theme-based learning project that demonstrates your ability to listen, talk, read, and write about a topic that interests you.
</>
<c>
102 83420
This course attempts to help students develop their skills in English reading, listening, writing, and speaking. Together we will be reading articles of various subjects to improve reading comprehension and vocabulary as the same time. Students will be encouraged to express their thoughts on the reading subjects and also on the topics they choose for their presentations. Two hours of each week will be spent on listening exercise. In addition, students will be asked to write and hand in three formal essays on assigned topics.
</>
