102 83420
This course attempts to help students develop their skills in English reading, listening, writing, and speaking. Together we will be reading articles of various subjects to improve reading comprehension and vocabulary as the same time. Students will be encouraged to express their thoughts on the reading subjects and also on the topics they choose for their presentations. Two hours of each week will be spent on listening exercise. In addition, students will be asked to write and hand in three formal essays on assigned topics.
</>
<c>
102 83420
This section of Freshman English is designed as an interactive and student-centered workshop to help students improve their listening, speaking, reading and writing abilities in English through various activities and exposure to a wide variety of materials in English. Using resources such as English interviews, news videos, newspaper and magazine articles, and intriguing talks on the Internet, we will focus on issues in the contemporary world. Students are expected to spend two to four hours a week to prepare for class, probably including reading an article, listening to an interview, or watching a video, in order to equip themselves with necessary knowledge and vocabulary for class discussion. In class, the topic of the week will be further explored through group presentations. We will have Writing workshop, Speech workshop, and Reading workshop in this semester. Finally, students need to give a 5-minute speech and a group presentation (60 minutes, including 10-minute/15-minute group discussions).
</>
