102 83420
The objective of this course is to enhance the reading and writing skills, listening and speaking ability of non-English majors.
</>
<c>
102 83420
This course is designed to help students improve their four skills in English. Various kinds of essays will be studied to improve students' reading ability. Audio-visual materials will be used to enhance students' listening ability. Writing exercises are designed to improve students' writing ability. There will be dialogue practices, discussion sessions, group reports and various presentations to encourage students to speak English.
</>
<c>
102 83420
During this three-hour course, you will read thought-provoking essays, engage in lively classroom discussion, and give short presentations. You will develop listening, thinking and speaking skills in English by doing a series of fun-filled activities under the guidance of your instructor. You will also learn to appreciate English poems, and even be inspired to commit a poem or two to memory.
</>
