102 23190
The course is a survey of British literature of the twentieth century. While we will begin at the turn of the century with the poetry of Hardy and Housman, the course will focus primarily on the Modernist period, especially on Joyce, Woolf, and Eliot, as well as on the artistic ferment of the avant-garde in the teens and the poetry that resulted from the disaster of the Great War. We will then survey some important poetry from the 30s through the 60s.
