102 42552
At the end of the course, students will achieve an Spanish B2.1 level. That means:
Students will be able to understand the main ideas of complex text on both concrete and abstract topics, including technical discussions in their field of specialisation. Moreover, they will be able to interact with a degree of fluency and spontaneity that will makes regular interaction with native speakers quite possible without strain for either party. Finally, they will able to produce clear, detailed text on a wide range of subjects and will explain a viewpoint on a topical issue giving the advantages and disadvantages of various options.
