This 2-credit required course serves as a roadmap for undergraduate students who are about to receive the professional education of library and information science. Information science is an interdisciplinary and multidisciplinary research domain. However, its origin, definition, scope and boundary are highly ambiguous. It is one of the most enthusiastically debated, appropriated, and participated research domains. This course will give you an orientation of information science from the LIS perspective.
