241 U1900
Introduction to marine biogeochemistry/chemical oceanography
The physical chemistry of seawater
Chemical equilibrium models for the composition of sea water: major and minor elements
Chemical speciation, composition, solubility and thermodynamic relationships and applications to marine biogeochemistry
Redox chemistry of sea water: Biological and geochemical cycling in the oceans
Nutrient cycling, speciation and their budgets in the ocean
Carbon cycling, speciation and their budgets in the ocean
CO2 system, alkalinity, calcite distribution and pH
Trace metals and primary production; the Iron Hypothesis
Marine organics and their role in chemical speciation and in processes affecting the fate of elements in the oceans
Radioisotopes and mixing times in the ocean
Topic studies of the seas around Taiwan
</>
