548 M0870
1.Biomechanics： Equilibrium, forces on hip, stress and strain, hydrostatics, viscosity and viscous flow, etc.
2.Exponential growth and decay：Exponential growth and decay
3.System of many particles：Microstates and macrostates, energy of a system, thermal equilibrium, entropy, Boltzmann factor, Nernst equation, chemical potential, Gibbs free energy, etc.
4.Transport in an infinite medium：Flux, continuity, solvent drag, diffusion, etc.
5.Transport through neutral membranes：Membrane, osmotic press, solute transport, artificial kidney, etc.
6.Impulses in nerve and muscle cell：Properties of nerves, electric field, charge distribution, leakage current, nerve impulse, electrotonus, Hodgkin-Huxley model, propagation, etc.
7.The exterior potential and the electrocardiogram：The exterior potential and the electrocardiogram
8.Biomagnetism：Biomagnetism
9.Electricity and magnetism at the cellular level：Electricity and magnetism at the cellular level
10.Biofeedback：Biofeedback
持續改善：因應每屆修課學生背景不同而調整授課內容或難易度
